Description: Limestone ostracon: with remains of seven lines of red-painted hieratic text, Chapter 68 of the 'Book of the Dead', on the verso and a further nine lines of text on the recto.
Curator's comments: For spells from the Book of the Dead on ostraca (very rare) cf. M. Heerma van Voss in 'Phoenix' 14 (1968), pp.165-71.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (135582) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/135582)
Associated titles: Inscription from: Book of the Dead (Chapter 68)
